00:44:01,223 --> 00:44:03,600
Yeah, that's right. Savino.

720
00:44:04,559 --> 00:44:06,478
You ain't never move no dope.

721
00:44:06,561 --> 00:44:08,104
You was always muscle as I recall.

722
00:44:09,523 --> 00:44:11,650
Now you musclin' for Mario, huh?

723
00:44:12,567 --> 00:44:14,236
I wasn't there.

724
00:44:14,319 --> 00:44:17,531
When they did the old man like that,
I wasn't there.

725
00:44:17,614 --> 00:44:20,492
Chris an' snoop, they on that.

726
00:44:20,575 --> 00:44:23,578
I know who was there.
So you innocent, huh?

727
00:44:25,497 --> 00:44:29,668
Let me ask you somethin' though,
bein' that you muscle for Mario.

728
00:44:29,751 --> 00:44:32,170
What you was gonna do
if you was there, huh?

729
00:44:32,254 --> 00:44:33,588
Riddle me that.

730
00:44:37,676 --> 00:44:39,302
Yeah.

731
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:45,267
You know what, yo?

732
00:44:55,151 --> 00:44:56,611
Ready?

733
00:44:56,778 --> 00:44:58,321
Yeah.

734
00:44:58,405 --> 00:44:59,781
A'ight.

735
00:45:05,287 --> 00:45:07,873
- Yeah?
- We gotta talk.

736
00:45:07,956 --> 00:45:10,250
- I'll come over to you.
- Hm.

737
00:45:14,296 --> 00:45:15,881
Does that seem possible?

738
00:45:15,964 --> 00:45:18,717
To go through the court system
with a false ID?

739
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:24,723
Maybe the first time, if she's got no
priors, no prints on file, but after that?

740
00:45:24,806 --> 00:45:27,767
Bpi sheets have fingerprint characteristics

741
00:45:27,851 --> 00:45:29,644
that are like an FBI bar code.

742
00:45:29,895 --> 00:45:31,646
And it's paired with a photo.

743
00:45:31,730 --> 00:45:35,150
A name's one thing,
but unless these women are twin sisters

744
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:38,987
and one's been carrying the other one's hand
around in her purse for the last 12 years...

745
00:45:39,446 --> 00:45:41,448
Somebody's yanking your chain.

746
00:45:44,284 --> 00:45:45,869
It's definitely a code.

747
00:45:45,952 --> 00:45:48,663
Definitely not having much to do with time.

748
00:45:48,788 --> 00:45:51,249
We're at a point where
I'm going to need more bodies,

749
00:45:51,333 --> 00:45:53,335
surveillance cars, man-hours.

750
00:45:53,501 --> 00:45:57,297
We're gonna have to stay on these guys
till those clocks start to make sense.

751
00:45:57,505 --> 00:46:00,342
Good news is they're giving me
more manpower than they can waste.

752
00:46:00,467 --> 00:46:02,469
- Bad news?
- It's all around the office

753
00:46:02,552 --> 00:46:05,513
that I'm giving out hours and money
to people to work other cases.

754
00:46:07,349 --> 00:46:09,684
I can't help it, Lester.
It's the kind of person I am.

755
00:46:09,768 --> 00:46:11,937
- I give and give.
- If you're not careful,

756
00:46:12,020 --> 00:46:14,439
you're gonna get shit on you, on us.

757
00:46:14,522 --> 00:46:16,232
Who's gonna complain?

758
00:46:16,316 --> 00:46:18,693
Guys are working cases and getting paid.

759
00:46:20,111 --> 00:46:21,571
So what exactly do you need?

760
00:46:22,822 --> 00:46:24,366
Seven men.

761
00:46:24,449 --> 00:46:26,326
No, eight. And cars.

762
00:46:26,660 --> 00:46:30,080
Oh, shit...
They offered me men from the districts,

763
00:46:30,163 --> 00:46:32,457
and a surveillance supervisor
to run the detail.

764
00:46:32,749 --> 00:46:34,417
Anyone in the districts we trust?

765
00:46:35,126 --> 00:46:37,379
Huh... let me think on that.

766
00:46:40,632 --> 00:46:41,716
Yeah?

767
00:46:41,800 --> 00:46:45,929
I don't know how the fuck did you
of all people do this shit, huh? How?

768
00:46:46,012 --> 00:46:49,099
- You got the right Allen wrench?
- Goddamn directions.

769
00:46:49,182 --> 00:46:51,184
What kind of scotch are you using?

770
00:46:59,901 --> 00:47:01,653
Ah, fuck!

771
00:47:01,736 --> 00:47:04,906
Fuck! Fuck! Piece of shit!

772
00:47:05,407 --> 00:47:08,910
Yo, so you talked to Chris, right?
What he say?

773
00:47:09,411 --> 00:47:11,162
He didn't say shit.

774
00:47:11,287 --> 00:47:13,207
He knows I ain't say
a fuckin' word to no police.

775
00:47:13,540 --> 00:47:17,002
And you heard what little dermell said
to the juvenile master?

776
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:21,339
Lady ax him like, "yo, you got a record?"
He's like "yeah, bitch, I got a record.

777
00:47:21,423 --> 00:47:24,884
"My record's so long
I'm about to put out an album."

778
00:47:25,927 --> 00:47:28,471
Uh-uh, uh-uh...
Don't touch that dial, young 'UN.

779
00:47:36,396 --> 00:47:38,023
This a Stanfield corner, huh?

780
00:47:42,068 --> 00:47:44,070
You know who I am?

781
00:47:51,453 --> 00:47:53,163
You make sure you tell the boss man

782
00:47:53,246 --> 00:47:56,041
that you know who it is
dropped savino last night.

783
00:47:56,124 --> 00:47:58,126
You feel me?

784
00:47:58,585 --> 00:48:01,504
You tell that man I'm-a drop all his muscle

785
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:05,383
until he get the heart to come
down to the street and dance.

786
00:48:07,635 --> 00:48:10,096
You gonna remember all that, sweet pea?

787
00:48:25,153 --> 00:48:29,240
- That's Omar? Damn.
- Savino dead, yo?

788
00:48:31,159 --> 00:48:35,455
Shit, man, if he woulda made me
from monk's apartment the other night,

789
00:48:36,372 --> 00:48:38,833
I might be laid out my own self.

790
00:48:39,793 --> 00:48:42,212
Gimpy as a motherfucker.

791
00:48:44,005 --> 00:48:47,425
I don't know, senator. I want to
believe you. I mean, I'm your lawyer.

792
00:48:47,509 --> 00:48:51,763
But there's all this up on the board
that Mr. Bond has on display -

793
00:48:51,846 --> 00:48:54,349
11,000 to West Side hoops,

794
00:48:54,516 --> 00:48:57,352
next day, $11,000 drawn.

795
00:48:57,811 --> 00:49:02,023
Then $11,000 deposited
in your personal banking account.

796
00:49:02,190 --> 00:49:06,069
You bet it all went into my account.
It made it easier for me to do my job.

797
00:49:06,402 --> 00:49:09,072
And at the end of the day,
not one penny stayed with me.

798
00:49:09,155 --> 00:49:11,491
I need you to do better than that, senator.

799
00:49:11,574 --> 00:49:13,493
- Where are your records?
- Records?

800
00:49:13,576 --> 00:49:19,707
Yes, records. For example, this check
for $11,000 dated January 22nd.

801
00:49:19,874 --> 00:49:21,709
That was last winter, right?

802
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:26,005
So, some went to pay everyone's bge,

803
00:49:26,297 --> 00:49:29,134
'cause half my district was
gonna have the heat turned off

804
00:49:29,217 --> 00:49:33,138
and then, some went for puff jackets
for them that got children in need.

805
00:49:33,221 --> 00:49:34,889
Let me tell you something, man.

806
00:49:35,306 --> 00:49:38,476
My neck of the woods,
it's a jungle out there.

807
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:43,231
Everybody living hand to mouth,
improvising, hustlin',

808
00:49:43,356 --> 00:49:45,400
make do with as little as you can imagine.

809
00:49:45,775 --> 00:49:48,611
Hell, that TV show, what the...

810
00:49:48,695 --> 00:49:50,488
Survivor?

811
00:49:50,572 --> 00:49:53,575
Man, they want some good contestants,
they need to come around West Side.

812
00:49:53,658 --> 00:49:57,287
Folks I know? We'd do great on that show.

813
00:49:57,829 --> 00:50:00,498
Practice every damn day of our lives.

814
00:50:00,915 --> 00:50:05,378
Hell, and fear factor? Aw, shit.
Don't even get me started.

815
00:50:05,587 --> 00:50:08,256
Forgive me, but I still don't understand
how that justifies...

816
00:50:08,339 --> 00:50:10,175
Let me tell you something, brother -

817
00:50:10,383 --> 00:50:13,219
I don't know how they do it
out in Roland park.

818
00:50:13,344 --> 00:50:17,098
Maybe prosecutor obonda
can enlighten me on that.

819
00:50:17,348 --> 00:50:21,936
But my world is strictly cash-and-carry,
and I am Clay Davis -

820
00:50:22,270 --> 00:50:24,772
my people need something,
they know where to find me.

821
00:50:26,441 --> 00:50:29,194
Let me tell you, brother,
I step out the door,

822
00:50:29,277 --> 00:50:32,030
hit the corner of mosher and Pennsylvania,

823
00:50:32,113 --> 00:50:33,865
you better believe my pockets are bulging.

824
00:50:33,948 --> 00:50:36,659
But by the time I get to Robert street...

825
00:50:38,328 --> 00:50:41,706
Objection! Objection, your honor.

826
00:50:43,291 --> 00:50:45,710
Senator! Senator, take a seat

827
00:50:45,793 --> 00:50:48,546
and refrain from off-hand references
to Mr. Bond.

828
00:50:48,630 --> 00:50:50,590
My apologies, your honor.

829
00:50:50,924 --> 00:50:54,177
But these charities were set up
for basketball leagues

830
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:55,970
in city rec centers, weren't they?

831
00:50:56,054 --> 00:51:01,100
Yeah, but you give me 20,000
for a basketball and an air pump,

832
00:51:01,184 --> 00:51:05,980
I am pullin' goodly on that
for whatever, whoever comes at me.

833
00:51:06,356 --> 00:51:10,151
"Senator Clay, I gots to Bury my mother,

834
00:51:10,485 --> 00:51:12,195
"bail out my son,

835
00:51:12,445 --> 00:51:15,406
"buy a new shirt for a job interview,

836
00:51:15,698 --> 00:51:18,534
"pay my child's asthma doctor."

837
00:51:18,660 --> 00:51:21,871
Takes me half an hour to go a hundred yards

838
00:51:21,955 --> 00:51:26,751
and excuse me if I didn't ask
that old arthritis woman for a receipt,

839
00:51:27,252 --> 00:51:31,756
or that young mother needed
the similac to sign a damn piece of paper

840
00:51:31,839 --> 00:51:33,925
so I don't have to be up here
in this box right now

841
00:51:34,008 --> 00:51:39,097
explainin' to folks who never been in
our neck of the woods how things truly are.

842
00:51:40,598 --> 00:51:43,434
And if a jury of my peers, you all,

843
00:51:43,518 --> 00:51:47,146
deem it right and true
for me to walk out of here

844
00:51:47,230 --> 00:51:49,399
an upright and justified man?

845
00:51:50,233 --> 00:51:52,277
I ain't gonna lie to you.

846
00:51:52,360 --> 00:51:55,321
I'm gonna do the same damn thing tomorrow,

847
00:51:55,405 --> 00:51:57,407
and the day after that
and the day after that,

848
00:51:57,532 --> 00:52:00,410
until they got me laid out
at march's funeral home,

849
00:52:00,493 --> 00:52:02,245
and truck me off to mount auburn.

850
00:52:08,459 --> 00:52:11,504
Silence. Silence in this courtroom.

851
00:52:11,838 --> 00:52:14,090
What about trailers? Like fema.

852
00:52:14,173 --> 00:52:16,801
We set up trailers to act as
temp housing for some of the...

853
00:52:16,884 --> 00:52:20,305
Some of the shelter population.
Put 'em down in war memorial Plaza.

854
00:52:20,471 --> 00:52:22,849
Do you know how much
fema pays per trailer?

855
00:52:23,141 --> 00:52:24,767
A dozen trailers for the homeless,

856
00:52:24,851 --> 00:52:27,478
we've got 3-4,000 on the streets, at least.

857
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:30,148
It's symbolic. You know,
we're doing what we can

858
00:52:30,231 --> 00:52:32,442
with a civic disaster - like New Orleans.

859
00:52:32,525 --> 00:52:35,361
Abandoned by the state,
ignored by the federal government.

860
00:52:35,445 --> 00:52:38,823
It's bad enough you want to keep
the city shelters open 24/7.

861
00:52:38,906 --> 00:52:42,493
That puts the health department
a couple of hundred thousand in the red.

862
00:52:42,577 --> 00:52:45,830
Add that to the overage
for letting the police department run wild

863
00:52:45,913 --> 00:52:49,834
- with overtime and investigative costs...
- There's no choice anymore.

864
00:52:49,917 --> 00:52:52,295
This thing has a lock
on everyone's attention.

865
00:52:52,378 --> 00:52:55,548
When another victim disappears,
we're gonna be even more on the spot.

866
00:52:55,631 --> 00:53:00,219
I'm just telling you, if this goes on more
than a month, with what we'll be spending,

867
00:53:00,303 --> 00:53:02,305
you're looking at cutbacks
throughout the agencies,

868
00:53:02,430 --> 00:53:04,932
maybe even teacher layoffs
come the end of the fiscal.

869
00:53:05,266 --> 00:53:08,019
- Teacher layoffs?
- By a gubernatorial candidate.

870
00:53:08,102 --> 00:53:11,189
- In an election year.
- Lovely.

871
00:53:20,281 --> 00:53:22,200
Hold up, hold up, hold up!

872
00:53:22,283 --> 00:53:25,411
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

873
00:53:25,495 --> 00:53:30,500
I just want to say that despite
all the false accusations made against me,

874
00:53:30,583 --> 00:53:33,711
the people who I continue to serve
have spoken.

875
00:53:33,795 --> 00:53:36,923
What the fuck just happened?

876
00:53:37,006 --> 00:53:40,551
As long as I
can to serve the people.

877
00:53:40,635 --> 00:53:43,346
Whatever it was,
they don't teach it in law school.

878
00:53:46,599 --> 00:53:49,852
45 inches of Clay Davis
playing not just the race card

879
00:53:49,936 --> 00:53:51,979
but the whole deck, coming at ya.

880
00:53:52,814 --> 00:53:54,190
Got it. Thank you.

881
00:53:54,524 --> 00:53:57,902
Someday you're going to have
to explain all this to me, Gus.

882
00:53:57,985 --> 00:54:01,489
After watching that verdict come in,
I feel very white.

883
00:54:02,865 --> 00:54:06,494
Well, start with some James brown records
and work up from there.

884
00:54:12,667 --> 00:54:13,960
It's embarrassing, ain't it?

885
00:54:14,043 --> 00:54:17,004
I can't believe nobody had
sense enough to tone this down.

886
00:54:17,088 --> 00:54:20,508
The hype is bad enough, but what gets me
is that I can't trust the guy.

887
00:54:20,758 --> 00:54:23,094
I send him back out on the street
to own his mistake,

888
00:54:23,177 --> 00:54:26,347
he comes back with some bullshit
about stolen identities.

889
00:54:26,431 --> 00:54:29,034
I don't give a fuck he gets took.
Everybody gets took now and then.

890
00:54:29,058 --> 00:54:32,186
- I know I did.
- It's about not owning up to it.

891
00:54:32,353 --> 00:54:35,273
Gus, this thing with the woman
and the crab cake?

892
00:54:35,356 --> 00:54:38,109
You think the first time you catch him
is the first time he does it?

893
00:54:38,192 --> 00:54:40,987
A lot of guys'll try to duck a correction

894
00:54:41,737 --> 00:54:45,783
but he was standing on an outright lie,
and if he'll lie about a correction...

895
00:54:45,908 --> 00:54:49,078
Then will he lie to make a story
better than it ought to be?

896
00:54:49,912 --> 00:54:53,499
I keep thinking about that kid in the
wheelchair out in front of oriole park.

897
00:54:53,583 --> 00:54:55,918
The one that only had a nickname.

898
00:54:57,253 --> 00:55:00,381
A black kid from the West Side,
crazy for baseball?

899
00:55:00,840 --> 00:55:02,758
Basketball, yeah.

900
00:55:02,884 --> 00:55:04,552
Football, sure.

901
00:55:06,637 --> 00:55:10,224
I don't wanna call another reporter a liar.
I really don't.

902
00:55:30,953 --> 00:55:33,080
What's the matter, baby?

903
00:55:36,417 --> 00:55:37,960
You can't sleep?

904
00:56:23,130 --> 00:56:25,049
Let's see.

905
00:56:25,132 --> 00:56:27,134
Let's say good night to everybody.

906
00:56:32,014 --> 00:56:33,724
Good night, moon.

907
00:56:36,978 --> 00:56:38,896
- You say it.
- Good night, moon.

908
00:56:38,980 --> 00:56:42,066
There you go. Good night, stars.

909
00:56:42,149 --> 00:56:44,151
Good night, stars.

910
00:56:45,820 --> 00:56:49,532
- Good night, po-pos.
- Good night, po-pos.

911
00:56:50,783 --> 00:56:54,036
- Good night, fiends.
- Good night, fiends.

912
00:56:54,620 --> 00:56:57,623
- Good night, hoppers.
- Good night, hoppers.

913
00:56:57,832 --> 00:57:01,502
- Good night, hustlers.
- Good night, hustlers.

914
00:57:01,961 --> 00:57:05,214
- Good night, scammers.
- Good night, scammers.

915
00:57:06,007 --> 00:57:10,094
- Good night to everybody.
- Good night to everybody.

916
00:57:10,177 --> 00:57:13,681
Good night to one and all.

917
00:57:13,806 --> 00:57:17,018
Good night to one and all.

